{"techStack":{"frontend":"Next.js 16, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS","backend":"Next.js API Routes (in-memory data store)","database":"In-memory store (module-level singleton Maps, no external database)","auth":"Cookie-based sessions (HttpOnly, server-side Map<token, userId>), plaintext passwords with upgrade comment","hosting":"Vercel (or any Node.js host)"},"fileTree":["src/lib/store.ts","src/lib/types.ts","src/lib/auth.ts","src/lib/seed.ts","src/lib/rank.ts","src/lib/notifications.ts","src/app/layout.tsx","src/app/page.tsx","src/app/login/page.tsx","src/app/register/page.tsx","src/app/accept-invite/page.tsx","src/app/dashboard/page.tsx","src/app/workspace/[workspaceId]/page.tsx","src/app/workspace/[workspaceId]/settings/page.tsx","src/app/board/[boardId]/page.tsx","src/app/api/auth/register/route.ts","src/app/api/auth/login/route.ts","src/app/api/auth/logout/route.ts","src/app/api/auth/me/route.ts","src/app/api/workspaces/route.ts","src/app/api/workspaces/[workspaceId]/route.ts","src/app/api/workspaces/[workspaceId]/boards/route.ts","src/app/api/workspaces/[workspaceId]/invites/route.ts","src/app/api/workspaces/[workspaceId]/invites/[inviteId]/route.ts","src/app/api/invites/accept/route.ts","src/app/api/boards/[boardId]/route.ts","src/app/api/columns/[columnId]/cards/route.ts","src/app/api/cards/[cardId]/route.ts","src/app/api/cards/[cardId]/comments/route.ts","src/app/api/comments/[commentId]/route.ts","src/app/api/notifications/route.ts","src/app/api/notifications/[notificationId]/read/route.ts","src/app/api/notifications/read-all/route.ts","src/components/KanbanBoard.tsx","src/components/KanbanColumn.tsx","src/components/CardTile.tsx","src/components/CardModal.tsx","src/components/CommentSection.tsx","src/components/InviteModal.tsx","src/components/NotificationBell.tsx","src/components/Navbar.tsx","src/hooks/useBoard.ts","src/hooks/useNotifications.ts"],"apiContracts":["POST /api/auth/register - { email: string, password: string, displayName: string } → 201 { user: { id, email, displayName, emailVerifiedAt } } | 409 { error: 'Email already registered' }","POST /api/auth/login - { email: string, password: string } → 200 { user: { id, email, displayName } } + sets HttpOnly cookie 'session_token' | 401 { error: 'Invalid credentials' }","POST /api/auth/logout - {} → 200 { ok: true } + clears session cookie","GET /api/auth/me - (cookie) → 200 { user: { id, email, displayName, avatarInitial } } | 401 { error: 'Unauthenticated' }","POST /api/workspaces - { name: string, slug: string } → 201 { workspace: { id, name, slug, createdBy } } | 409 { error: 'Slug already taken' } | 422 { error: 'Slug must be 3-40 URL-safe characters' }","GET /api/workspaces/[workspaceId] - (cookie) → 200 { workspace: { id, name, slug }, members: [{ userId, displayName, role, joinedAt }], pendingInvites: [{ id, email, expiresAt }] } | 403 { error: 'Not a member' }","GET /api/workspaces/[workspaceId]/boards - (cookie) → 200 { boards: [{ id, name, createdAt, archivedAt }] } | 403 { error: 'Not a member' }","POST /api/workspaces/[workspaceId]/boards - { name: string } → 201 { board: { id, name, workspaceId, columns: [{ id, name, rank }] } } | 403 { error: 'Not a member' }","POST /api/workspaces/[workspaceId]/invites - { email: string } → 201 { invite: { id, email, token, expiresAt } } | 403 { error: 'Only owners can invite' } | 409 { error: 'Invite already pending for this email' }","DELETE /api/workspaces/[workspaceId]/invites/[inviteId] - (cookie) → 200 { ok: true } | 403 { error: 'Only owners can revoke invites' } | 404 { error: 'Invite not found' }","POST /api/invites/accept - { token: string, password?: string, displayName?: string } → 200 { workspace: { id, slug } } | 410 { error: 'Invite expired. Request a new one.' } | 404 { error: 'Invalid invite token' }","GET /api/boards/[boardId] - (cookie) → 200 { board: { id, name, workspaceId }, columns: [{ id, name, rank, cards: [{ id, title, description, rank, dueDate, assigneeId, assigneeName, archivedAt, createdAt }] }] } | 403 | 404","PATCH /api/boards/[boardId] - { name?: string, archivedAt?: string|null } → 200 { board: { id, name, archivedAt } } | 403 { error: 'Not a member' }","DELETE /api/boards/[boardId] - (cookie, owner only) → 200 { ok: true } | 403 { error: 'Only owners can delete boards' }","POST /api/columns/[columnId]/cards - { title: string, description?: string, dueDate?: string, assigneeId?: string } → 201 { card: { id, columnId, title, description, rank, dueDate, assigneeId, createdAt } } | 422 { error: 'Title required (1-255 chars)' }","GET /api/cards/[cardId] - (cookie) → 200 { card: { id, columnId, boardId, title, description, rank, dueDate, assigneeId, assigneeName, archivedAt, createdAt, updatedAt } } | 403 | 404","PATCH /api/cards/[cardId] - { title?: string, description?: string, columnId?: string, rank?: string, assigneeId?: string|null, dueDate?: string|null, archivedAt?: string|null } → 200 { card } | 422 { error: string } | 403","DELETE /api/cards/[cardId] - (cookie, soft-archive) → 200 { ok: true, card: { id, archivedAt } } | 403","GET /api/cards/[cardId]/comments?page=1 - (cookie) → 200 { comments: [{ id, body, authorId, authorName, authorInitial, createdAt, editedAt }], total: number, page: number, pageSize: 20 }","POST /api/cards/[cardId]/comments - { body: string } → 201 { comment: { id, body, authorId, authorName, createdAt } } | 422 { error: 'Comment body required (max 2000 chars)' }","PATCH /api/comments/[commentId] - { body: string } → 200 { comment: { id, body, editedAt } } | 403 { error: 'Only comment author can edit' }","DELETE /api/comments/[commentId] - (cookie) → 200 { ok: true } | 403 { error: 'Only author or workspace owner can delete' }","GET /api/notifications - (cookie) → 200 { notifications: [{ id, type, referenceId, referenceType, read, createdAt, message: string }] }","PATCH /api/notifications/[notificationId]/read - (cookie) → 200 { ok: true }","PATCH /api/notifications/read-all - (cookie) → 200 { ok: true }"],"designDecisions":["WHAT: Single store.ts module with Map<id, Entity> for every entity. WHY: Zero-setup, fully synchronous, no connection pooling, satisfies hard constraint. Maps give O(1) lookups by ID. UPGRADE PATH: Replace each Map operation with a Prisma client call; the API route logic stays identical since store functions have the same signatures.","WHAT: Plaintext passwords stored in the User map with a // TODO comment. WHY: Hard constraint prohibits external auth services and crypto libraries. This is demo-only. UPGRADE PATH: Use Node.js built-in crypto.pbkdf2Sync() — zero external dependencies — to hash passwords on write and verify on login.","WHAT: Cookie-based sessions using a Map<token, userId> with crypto.randomUUID() tokens. WHY: HttpOnly cookies prevent XSS token theft. randomUUID() is built into Node 18+ (no external dependency). UPGRADE PATH: Replace Map with Redis SET with TTL; swap cookie for JWT plus refresh-token pattern described in PRD.","WHAT: Simulated real-time via polling (useBoard hook polls GET /api/boards/[boardId] every 3 seconds) instead of WebSockets. WHY: True WebSocket pub/sub requires Redis and a persistent server process — both excluded by hard constraints. Polling delivers 'good enough' real-time for demo. UPGRADE PATH: Add a /api/boards/[boardId]/events SSE route backed by Redis pub/sub as described in PRD; swap useBoard hook to EventSource.","WHAT: Fractional string rank (e.g., 'a', 'b', ... 'am') computed in rank.ts utility. WHY: Enables card reordering without renumbering all siblings. A simple midpoint-string algorithm (no external lib) handles the common insert-between case. UPGRADE PATH: Replace with LexoRank library for production-grade collision resistance.","WHAT: Invite tokens are crypto.randomUUID() stored directly in the Invite map (plaintext). WHY: No HMAC library available under hard constraints. For demo scope, UUID is unguessable enough. UPGRADE PATH: Use Node built-in crypto.createHmac('sha256', SECRET).update(inviteId).digest('hex') and store only the hash, validating on accept.","WHAT: Email 'sending' is console.log() with full email content. WHY: Zero external services. The log output lets the demo flow work (copy the invite link from server logs). UPGRADE PATH: Swap the sendEmail() stub in notifications.ts for a fetch() call to SendGrid or Postmark API.","WHAT: Drag-and-drop for card reordering uses the HTML5 native Drag and Drop API (onDragStart, onDragOver, onDrop) with no external libraries. WHY: Browser-native API requires zero dependencies and works across modern browsers. UPGRADE PATH: No change needed; the rank update PATCH calls remain identical.","WHAT: Board detail page is a client component using SWR-style polling. WHY: Drag-and-drop requires browser APIs (mousedown, touch events) so SSR is not viable for the board view. Other pages (dashboard, workspace settings) use server components with cookie reads for faster initial paint. UPGRADE PATH: No change needed; add WebSocket layer transparently.","WHAT: All permission checks are server-side in API routes by looking up WorkspaceMember records. WHY: UI hiding is not security. Every mutating endpoint calls assertMember(workspaceId, userId) before any write. UPGRADE PATH: Extract to middleware once route count grows.","WHAT: Fixed 3 columns (To Do, In Progress, Done) auto-created per board. WHY: Matches PRD MVP scope, eliminates rank-conflict surface area for columns, simplifies board creation. UPGRADE PATH: Remove is_system flag check and expose POST/PATCH/DELETE /columns routes.","WHAT: Icons are inline SVG elements rendered directly in JSX. WHY: Zero external icon library dependencies; raw Tailwind classes style them via className. UPGRADE PATH: Replace with any icon library by swapping the SVG elements."],"knownLimitations":["Data is lost on server restart — all users, boards, cards, and comments exist only in Node.js process memory. This is by design for the MVP demo.","No true real-time: board updates use 3-second polling, not WebSockets. Two users moving cards simultaneously will see each other's changes within ~3 seconds, not sub-1-second as specified in the PRD.","Email delivery is console.log() only — invite links and assignment notifications appear in the terminal, not in any inbox. The accept-invite flow still works by copying the logged URL.","Invite tokens and session tokens are not cryptographically signed (HMAC) — they use UUID v4 which is unguessable but not tamper-proof. Do not use in production.","No email verification enforcement in the demo — emailVerifiedAt is set automatically on registration so users can access boards immediately. The verification flow is scaffolded but not gated.","Passwords are stored as plaintext in the in-memory Map. This is intentional for the zero-dependency demo; upgrade to Node.js built-in crypto.pbkdf2Sync() before any real deployment."],"seedData":"On server start, seed.ts creates: (1) Two users — alice@demo.com / password123 (display: 'Alice Chen', owner) and bob@demo.com / password123 (display: 'Bob Torres', member). (2) One workspace — 'Acme Corp' with slug 'acme'. Both users are members; Alice is owner. (3) Two boards — 'Product Roadmap' and 'Marketing Q3'. (4) Each board gets 3 fixed columns: To Do (rank 1), In Progress (rank 2), Done (rank 3). (5) Product Roadmap board has 6 sample cards spread across columns: 'Design system audit' (In Progress, assigned Alice, due 3 days ago — triggers overdue indicator), 'API rate limiting' (To Do, assigned Bob), 'User onboarding flow' (In Progress, assigned Bob, due in 7 days), 'Fix login redirect bug' (Done, assigned Alice), 'Write Q3 OKRs' (To Do, unassigned), 'Performance benchmarking' (Done, assigned Bob). (6) 'Design system audit' card has 2 seed comments from Alice and Bob demonstrating the comment thread. (7) Bob has one unread notification: card_assigned for 'API rate limiting'."}